The paper is about visual saliency detection using a CNN architecture and pre-training on a large-scale dataset. This topic falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions learning high-level semantics, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its model on two datasets, which involves information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques.
